Inference for NGARCH model with standard EPD innovations - Frequentist approach

Emmanuel Djanga

9/16/2019

Source code used to implement one of the models as well as two case studies mentioned in the dissertation of the author.

library(knitr)
library(ucminf)
library(xtable)
library(robustbase)

Functions

expit <- function(x){
  num <- exp(x)
  denom <- 1+exp(x)
  return(num/denom)
}
K_EP <- function(x,log=FALSE){
    if(log==FALSE){
      denom <- 2*x^(1/x)*gamma(1+1/x)
      return(1/denom)
    }
    else{
      value <- log(2)+log(x)/x+lgamma(1+1/x)
      return(-value)
    }
}
alpha_star <- function(beta,log=FALSE){
    alpha <- beta[1]
    p1 <- beta[2]
    if(log==FALSE){
      num <- alpha*K_EP(p1)
      denom <- alpha*K_EP(p1)+(1-alpha)*K_EP(p1)
      return(num/denom)
    }
    else{
      term1 <- log(alpha)+K_EP(p1,log=TRUE)
      term2 <- log(alpha*K_EP(p1,log=FALSE)+(1-alpha)*K_EP(p1,log=FALSE))
      return(term1-term2) 
    }
}
B_AEP <- function(beta,log=FALSE){
    alpha <- beta[1]
    p1 <- beta[2]
    if(log==FALSE){
      num <- alpha*K_EP(p1,FALSE)
      denom <- alpha_star(beta)
      return(num/denom) 
    }
    else{
      term1 <- log(alpha)+K_EP(p1,TRUE)
      term2 <- alpha_star(beta,TRUE)
      return(term1-term2)
    }
}
mean_AEP <- function(beta){
    alpha <- beta[1]
    p1 <- beta[2]
    const <- 1/B_AEP(beta,FALSE)
    num1 <- (1-alpha)^2*p1*gamma(2/p1)
    denom1 <- gamma(1/p1)^2
    num2 <- alpha^2*p1*gamma(2/p1)
    denom2 <- gamma(1/p1)^2
    return(const*(num1/denom1-num2/denom2))
}
variance_AEP <- function(beta){
    alpha <- beta[1]
    p1 <- beta[2]
    const <- (1/B_AEP(beta,FALSE))^2
    num1 <- (1-alpha)^3*p1^2*gamma(3/p1)
    denom1 <- gamma(1/p1)^3
    num2 <- alpha^3*p1^2*gamma(3/p1)
    denom2 <- gamma(1/p1)^3
    return(const*(num1/denom2+num2/denom2)-mean_AEP(beta)^2)
}
pdf_AEP <- function(y,beta,log=FALSE){
    alpha <- beta[1]
    p1 <- beta[2]
    if(log==FALSE){
      ifelse(y<=0,(alpha/alpha_star(beta))*K_EP(p1)*exp(-(1/p1)*abs(y/(2*alpha_star(beta)))^p1),((1-alpha)/(1-alpha_star(beta)))*K_EP(p1)*exp(-(1/p1*abs(y/(2*(1-alpha_star(beta))))^p1)))
    }
    else{
      ifelse(y<=0,(log(alpha)-alpha_star(beta,TRUE))+K_EP(p1,TRUE)-(abs(y/(2*alpha_star(beta))))^p1/p1,(log(1-alpha)-log(1-alpha_star(beta)))+K_EP(p1,TRUE)-(abs(y/(2*(1-alpha_star(beta)))))^p1/p1)
    }
}
raepd <- function(T,alpha,p1,mu,sigma){
  beta_ <- c(alpha,p1);
  U <- runif(T,0,1)
  Y1 <- rgamma(T,1/beta_[2])
  Y2 <- rgamma(T,1/beta_[2])
  helper1 <- beta_[1]*sigma*(sign(U-beta_[1])-1)*Y1^(1/beta_[2])
  helper1 <- helper1/(2*B_AEP(beta_,FALSE)*gamma(1+1/beta_[2]))
  helper2 <- (1-beta_[1])*sigma*(sign(U-beta_[1])+1)*Y2^(1/beta_[2])
  helper2 <- helper2/(2*B_AEP(beta_,FALSE)*gamma(1+1/beta_[2]))
  X <- mu+helper1+helper2
  return(X)
}
# Setting
# N set to 200 but can be easily changed to 100
# p is set to 1.75 (platykurtic case) but can be easily changed to 3 (leptokurtic case)
T <- 750; N <- 200; MLE <- matrix(0,nrow=N,ncol=7); SE <- matrix(0,nrow=N,ncol=7); MSE <- matrix(0,nrow=N,ncol=7);
UB <- matrix(0,nrow=N,ncol=7); LB <- matrix(0,nrow=N,ncol=7); Length_CI <- matrix(0,nrow=N,ncol=7); cv <- abs(qnorm(0.5*(1-0.95))); count <- 1;
# True parameters
b0__ <- 1; b1__ <- 0.5; b2__ <- 0.3; c__ <- 0.1; alpha__ <- 0.5; p__ <- 3;
m__ <- 0.7; 
true_par <- c(b0__,b1__,b2__,c__,alpha__,p__,m__);
# Initial guess
parameters <- c(0,log(0.5),log(0.3),log(0.1),0,2,0.7) 
# Inference
while(count<(N+1)){
  set.seed(2*count)
  zt <- raepd(T,alpha__,p__,0,1)
  sigma2 <- rep(0,T)
  sigma2[1] <- b0__/(1-b1__-b2__*(1+c__^2))
  for(j in 2:T){
    sigma2[j] <- b0__+b1__*sigma2[j-1]+b2__*sigma2[j-1]*(zt[j-1]-c__)^2
  }
  rt <- sqrt(sigma2)*zt+m__
  logLikeh2od <- function(theta){
    beta <- theta[5:6] # Vector containing alpha, p1 and p2
    m <- theta[7]
    # Reparametrisation of initial parameters
    b1 <- exp(theta[2]) 
    b2 <- exp(theta[3])
    b0 <- exp(theta[1])
    c <- exp(theta[4]) # Leverage effect parameter
    if((b2*(1+c^2)+b1)<1){
      alpha <- expit(beta[1])
      p1 <- exp(beta[2])
      beta_rep <- c(alpha,p1)
      #Sigma2 
      sigma2_aux <- rep(0,T)
      sigma2_aux[1] <- b0/(1-b1-b2*(1+c^2))
      for(k in 2:T){
        sigma2_aux[k] <- b0+b1*sigma2_aux[k-1]+b2*(rt[k-1]-m-c*sqrt(sigma2_aux[k-1]))^2
      }
      helper <- mean_AEP(beta_rep)+sqrt(variance_AEP((beta_rep)))*(rt-m)/sqrt(sigma2_aux) # omega+delta*(r_t-m)/sigma_t present in the reference
      log_pdf_AEP_helper <- pdf_AEP(helper,beta_rep,log=TRUE)
      ll <- sum(log(sqrt(variance_AEP(beta_rep)))+log_pdf_AEP_helper-log(sqrt(sigma2_aux)))
      return(-ll)
    }
    else return(Inf)
  }
  optimisationResults <- ucminf(parameters,logLikeh2od,hessian = 2,control=list(maxeval=1000)) 
  estimate <- optimisationResults$par
  MLE[count,] <- c(exp(estimate[c(1,2,3,4)]),expit(estimate[5]),exp(estimate[6]),estimate[7])
  # SE - Delta method
  helper_DM <- diag(ucminf(parameters,logLikeh2od,hessian = 2)$invhessian)
  SE[count,c(1,2,3,4,6)]<-sqrt(helper_DM[c(1,2,3,4,6)]*MLE[count,c(1,2,3,4,6)]^2)
  SE[count,5] <- sqrt(helper_DM[5]*(exp(estimate[5])/(1+exp(estimate[5]))^2)^2)
  SE[count,7] <- sqrt(helper_DM[7])
  UB[count,] <- MLE[count,]+cv*SE[count,]
  LB[count,] <- MLE[count,]-cv*SE[count,]
  Length_CI[count,] <- UB[count,]-LB[count,]
  MSE[count,] <- (MLE[count,]-true_par)^2
  count <- count+1
}
final_matrix <- cbind(colMeans(MLE),colMedians(MLE),colMeans(MSE),colMeans(SE),colMeans(Length_CI))
rownames_ <- c("b0_","b1_","b2_","c_","alpha_","p_","m_")
row.names(final_matrix) <- rownames_
colnames_ <- c("Mean","Median","MSE","SE","Length C.I.")
row.names(final_matrix) <- rownames_
colnames(final_matrix) <- colnames_
table <- kable(final_matrix,digits=4)

#Comparison of rt__ and rt_fit
sigma2_fit <- rep(0,T)
MLE_fit <- as.numeric(final_matrix[,1])
sigma2_fit[1] <- MLE_fit[1]/(1-MLE_fit[2]-MLE_fit[3])
for(i in 2:T){
  sigma2_fit[i] <- MLE_fit[1]+MLE_fit[2]*sigma2_fit[i-1]+MLE_fit[3]*sigma2_fit[i-1]*(zt[i-1]-MLE_fit[4])^2
}
rt_fit <- sqrt(sigma2_fit)*zt+MLE_fit[7]
hist(rt, breaks = 100 ,probability=T,xlab="Data",ylim=c(0,0.4),main=NULL)
